Working with Large Data

Source: vignettes/articles/bigger-data.Rmd
bigger-data.Rmd


These files come from Centene Corporation’s Transparency in Coverage site.


library(dplyr)
library(purrr)
library(dm)
library(defogger)

Final TOC Table 

toc_url_centene <- dplyr::full_join(centene_toc_urls, 
                                    centene_toc_qualchoice_subs, 
                                    by = c("entity", 
                                           "sub_entity", 
                                           "type", 
                                           "origin"), copy = TRUE) |> 
                   dplyr::relocate(sub_index, .after = "sub_entity")

Build the Centene RESP Table 

toc_resp_centene <- toc_url_centene |> 
                    dplyr::select(origin) |>
                    dplyr::distinct() |> 
                    tibble::deframe() |> 
                    purrr::map_dfr(defog_toc)

toc_resp_centene <- toc_resp_centene |> 
                    dplyr::rename(type = rate_type) |> 
                    dplyr::mutate(entity = dplyr::case_when(
                    entity == "Centene Management Company LLC" ~ "Centene", 
                    TRUE ~ entity))

Creating a Relational Database with dm

You can build a relational database in R with the {dm} package, using only data frames in your R environment. Once your data model is complete, you can deploy it to a range of database management systems (DBMS). First, we need to create a dm object:

dm_centene_no_keys <- dm::dm(toc_url_centene, toc_resp_centene)
#> ── Metadata ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#> Tables: `toc_url_centene`, `toc_resp_centene`
#> Columns: 14
#> Primary keys: 0
#> Foreign keys: 0



Next, we need to define the primary keys:

dm::dm_enum_pk_candidates(dm = dm_centene_no_keys, table = toc_url_centene)
#> # A tibble: 5 × 3
#>   columns    candidate why                                   
#>   <keys>     <lgl>     <chr>                                 
#> 1 origin     TRUE      ""                                    
#> 2 entity     FALSE     "has duplicate values: Centene (12)"  
#> 3 sub_entity FALSE     "has duplicate values: QualChoice (7)"
#> 4 sub_index  FALSE     "has 6 missing values"                
#> 5 type       FALSE     "has duplicate values: toc (12)"
dm_centene_only_pks <- dm_centene_no_keys |> dm::dm_add_pk(table = toc_url_centene, columns = origin)
#> ── Metadata ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#> Tables: `toc_url_centene`, `toc_resp_centene`
#> Columns: 14
#> Primary keys: 1
#> Foreign keys: 0



Now, we need to link the two tables by a foreign key:

dm::dm_enum_fk_candidates(dm = dm_centene_only_pks, table = toc_resp_centene, ref_table = toc_url_centene)
#> # A tibble: 9 × 3
#>   columns          candidate why                                                
#>   <keys>           <lgl>     <chr>                                              
#> 1 origin           TRUE      ""                                                 
#> 2 id               FALSE     "Can't combine `value1` <integer> and `value1` <ch…
#> 3 plan_name        FALSE     "values of `toc_resp_centene$plan_name` not in `to…
#> 4 plan_id_type     FALSE     "values of `toc_resp_centene$plan_id_type` not in …
#> 5 plan_id          FALSE     "values of `toc_resp_centene$plan_id` not in `toc_…
#> 6 plan_market_type FALSE     "values of `toc_resp_centene$plan_market_type` not…
#> 7 entity           FALSE     "values of `toc_resp_centene$entity` not in `toc_u…
#> 8 type             FALSE     "values of `toc_resp_centene$type` not in `toc_url…
#> 9 location         FALSE     "values of `toc_resp_centene$location` not in `toc…
dm_centene_all_keys <- dm_centene_only_pks |> dm::dm_add_fk(table = toc_resp_centene, columns = origin, ref_table = toc_url_centene)
#> ── Metadata ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#> Tables: `toc_url_centene`, `toc_resp_centene`
#> Columns: 14
#> Primary keys: 1
#> Foreign keys: 1



Visualizing the Data Model 

dm_centene_no_keys |> dm::dm_draw(rankdir = "TB", view_type = "all")
dm_centene_only_pks |> dm::dm_draw(rankdir = "TB", view_type = "all")
dm_centene_all_keys |> dm::dm_draw(rankdir = "LR", view_type = "all")



Out-of-Network Files 


centene_oon_urls <- centene_toc_resp |> 
                    dplyr::filter(type == "out_of_network") |> 
                    dplyr::select(location) |> 
                    dplyr::distinct() |> 
                    tibble::deframe()
#> Error in dplyr::filter(centene_toc_resp, type == "out_of_network"): object 'centene_toc_resp' not found
#> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'centene_oon_urls' not found



centene_oon_files <- centene_oon_urls |> 
                     purrr::map_dfr(defog_oon)
#> Error in map(.x, .f, ...): object 'centene_oon_urls' not found
#> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'centene_oon_files' not found
dm_centene_oon <- dm::dm(centene_oon_files)
#> Error in .f(.x[[i]], ...): object 'centene_oon_files' not found
dm::dm_enum_pk_candidates(dm = dm_centene_oon, table = centene_oon_files)
#> Error in is_dm(dm): object 'dm_centene_oon' not found
